30/12/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Economy Minister Fatmir Besimi said Wednesday (29 December) that Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski has set up a team of experts to prepare the government's strategy for upcoming talks with the IMF. 
The team is to draft the strategy by February, when the IMF mission will arrive. 
One team member, Taki Fiti, said structural reforms are the most important tool for solving the country's economic problems.
In other news Wednesday, parliament adopted the state budget for 2005. 
Finance Minister Nikola Popovski said the main objectives are to maintain macroeconomic stability, boost growth and reforms, stabilise the debt and boost foreign investment. 
(MIA - 29/12/04)
